Sequential steps to install Nginx using Custom Script Extension:

1. Go to VM in Azure Portal
2. Select “Extensions + Applications”
3. Click “Add” → Custom Script Extension
4. Provide script

Example script:
#!/bin/bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx

5. Apply and run extension

Nginx is used as a web server to serve web pages.

A real-life use case is hosting websites or APIs.

Another example is using Nginx as a reverse proxy for applications.

Custom Script Extension automates configuration tasks.
